title: Astrobotic wins NASA funding for CubeRover mission
summary: Astrobotic, a company developing landers and other lunar technologies, has secured NASA funding to fly a small rover on a future mission to test its ability to survive the lunar night.

title: Scout Space and university labs win contracts for on-orbit servicing project
summary: Scout Space, a startup developing technologies for in-space services, won two U.S. Space Force contracts in support of the debris-cleanup project known as Orbital Prime

title: Starship uncrewed lunar lander test a “skeleton” of crewed lander
summary: A SpaceX Starship that will land on the moon an on uncrewed test flight may only be a “skeleton” of the version of that will carry people on the Artemis 3 mission, NASA says.

title: NASA, Rice University Mark 60th Anniversary of John F. Kennedy Speech
summary: NASA and Rice University in Houston will host multiple events in September to celebrate the 60th anniversary of John F. Kennedy’s historic speech at Rice Stadium, rallying the nation to land astronauts on the Moon before the end of the decade and bring the crew safely back to Earth.
